      • meetsRequirement

        public static boolean meetsRequirement(QuestPlayer player,
                                       java.lang.String requirement)
        Quests requirements are a little more dynamic than they used to be. Instead of just having a 'did they do this quest' requirement, you have either a 'did they do this quest' or 'are they currently doing this quest' requirement. In addition, you can have a list of requirements with ANDS and ORs between them. Still additionally, you can then specify keys required from another quest. The syntax is as follows:

        OperationSyntaxDescription
        ORQ1 | Q2The player has to have completed either Q1 or Q2
        ANDQ1 & Q2The player has to have completed both Q1 and Q2
        CURRENT*Q1The player must currently be doing Q1
        KEYSQ1.acThe player must have both keys a and c from quest Q1 and have finished Q1

        From these rules, complex expressions may be formed. Order of precedence is the order of the operations listed in the table, except for KEYS; KEYS is broken down into two sub expressions, as detailed below. Anywhere where a simple Q1 or Q2 is listed below (except in the case of the KEYS operation) may be substituted for another expression. For example, Q1 | Q2 & Q3 is valid, and stands for 'Finished Q1 or Finished both Q2 and Q3.' More complex examples are below.

        It's important to note that keys are treated seperately from quests. Regardless of if the requirement lists that the player needs to be currently doing a quest or if it says it needed to have been completed already, the key check is done regardless of if such statement is true. These statements are treated almost as if two seperate expressions in the form

        quest1.ab <==> (player has key quest1.a & player has key quest1.b & player has done quest 1)
        Similarly, if an * were to be put before the quest, the last part of the expression would change to is doing rather than has done.

        Examples

        • Player should have completed the quest "Quest For Money": Quest For Money
        • Player should have either completed the quest "Quest For Money" or be doing it now: Quest For Money|*Quest For Money
        • Player should have completed the quest "Quest For Money" or gotten key 'a' from the quest "Quest For Glory": Quest For Money|Quest For Glory.a
        • Player should have completed any of the following: "Quest For Money", "Quest For Glory", "Quest For Questing": Quest For Money|Quest For Glory|Quest For Questing
        Parameters:
        player -
        requirement -
        Returns:
